	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Vafþrúðnismál</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Vafþrúðnismál#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Vafþrúðnismál#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Eddic poem</div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg/220px-Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="thumbimage" srcset="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg/330px-Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg 1.5x, http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg/440px-Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg 2x" data-file-width="935" data-file-height="702" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Odin_and_Vaf%C3%BEr%C3%BA%C3%B0nir_by_Fr%C3%B8lich.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Odin and Vafþrúðnir battle in a game of knowledge (1895) by <a href="Lorenz_Frølich" title="Lorenz Frølich">Lorenz Frølich</a>.</div></div></div>
<p><i><b>Vafþrúðnismál</b></i> (<a href="Old_Norse" title="Old Norse">Old Norse</a>: "The Lay of <a href="Vafþrúðnir" title="Vafþrúðnir">Vafþrúðnir</a>")<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOrchard1997170_1-0" class="reference"><a href="Vafþrúðnismál#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOrchard1997170-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is the third poem in the <i><a href="Poetic_Edda" title="Poetic Edda">Poetic Edda</a></i>. It is a conversation in verse form conducted initially between the <a href="Æsir" title="Æsir">Æsir</a> <a href="Odin" title="Odin">Odin</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frigg" title="Frigg">Frigg</a>, and subsequently between Odin and the giant Vafþrúðnir. The poem goes into detail about the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norse_cosmogony" class="mw-redirect" title="Norse cosmogony">Norse cosmogony</a> and was evidently used extensively as a source document by <a href="Snorri_Sturluson" title="Snorri Sturluson">Snorri Sturluson</a> in the construction of the <i><a href="Prose_Edda" title="Prose Edda">Prose Edda</a></i> who quotes it. The poem is preserved in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Codex_Regius" title="Codex Regius">Codex Regius</a> and partially in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AM_748_I_4to" title="AM 748 I 4to">AM 748 I 4to</a>. There are preservation problems relating to stanzas 40-41.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
